cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with natural language understanding in multi-turn dialogs, which falls under the scope of cs.CL.
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The use of neural architecture for incorporating dialog history and improving performance in natural language understanding aligns with the scope of cs.AI.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The use of neural networks and memory networks in the proposed architecture falls under the scope of cs.LG.
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The use of neural networks in the proposed architecture aligns with the scope of cs.NE.
5. cs.SD (Sound) - Although less likely, the use of speaker-sensitive encoding could potentially be related to sound processing, which falls under the scope of cs.SD.
